50|$|The Fair <b>Credit</b> <b>Reporting</b> Act (FCRA) of 1970 {{regulates the}} collection, sharing, {{and use of}} customer-credit information. The act allows {{consumers}} to obtain a copy of their <b>credit</b> <b>report</b> from <b>credit</b> bureaus that hold information on them, provides for consumers to dispute negative information held and sets time limits, after which negative information is suppressed. It requires that consumers be informed when negative information is added to their credit records, and when adverse action is taken based on a <b>credit</b> <b>report.</b>|$|R
